01:01:54,140 --> 01:01:56,779
Whatever he is, he's a damn problem.

706
01:02:09,700 --> 01:02:10,815
MASU: Oh, my God.

707
01:02:10,900 --> 01:02:13,937
FORREST: I stocked this place up
a couple of years ago.

708
01:02:14,580 --> 01:02:15,808
Just in case.

709
01:02:16,060 --> 01:02:17,413
In case of what?

710
01:02:17,540 --> 01:02:20,134
In case you declare war
on some small country?

711
01:02:20,380 --> 01:02:21,335
Yeah.

712
01:02:30,140 --> 01:02:31,289
What are you doing?

713
01:02:31,380 --> 01:02:32,733
This is a com unit.

714
01:02:32,820 --> 01:02:35,015
I know they're coming to look for me.

715
01:02:35,540 --> 01:02:37,212
And if l keep a signal...

716
01:02:37,780 --> 01:02:39,532
...they'll be able to find me...

717
01:02:39,620 --> 01:02:41,531
...and that's just what I want.

718
01:02:51,620 --> 01:02:53,133
Bingo. l've got something.

719
01:02:53,220 --> 01:02:54,335
Six-two degrees...

720
01:02:54,420 --> 01:02:57,253
...nine minutes by 148 degrees even.

721
01:02:57,540 --> 01:03:00,930
l know that country. A chopper's not going
to do us much good.

722
01:03:01,460 --> 01:03:03,371
We need to get in there on horseback.

723
01:03:03,460 --> 01:03:06,452
Get on the radio, Spinks.
Get us some horses up there.

724
01:03:06,700 --> 01:03:10,613
STONE: Let's take the chopper back up
